race.comment: BONS TO RICHES (1) has been patiently handled, and looks set for another good prep after letting down strongly to win fresh up at Kyneton 3 weeks ago in a soft field. He has a kinder draw here, and with a kilo less to carry, he is good enough to repeat the dose. INSAIN HARRY (10) went close to breaking through last season, and then switched stables over his break. He resumed with an end-to-end win at Werribee 17 days ago, and is likely to take some pegging back in this as well. BOLD RESPONSE (2) is a handy gelding when fit, and he is close to his peak third up from a spell. He has a draw upgrade from his last run, and with the aid of a 4kg claim, he can figure in the top 3 here. TENNESSEE SONG (11) and ALPINE FOX (6) are both last start winner that should be included in all top 4 combos here.
